description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 6 Occupational Therapy Rotation – Whipps Cross Hospital &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Develop your clinical skills with complex co-morbidity in a friendly supportive environment!&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you an experienced Band 5 Occupational Therapist looking for the next challenge or Band 6 Occupational Therapist keen to develop clinical &amp; leadership skills across wide and varied settings? Our Whipps Cross Hospital Band 6 rotation provides the perfect opportunity for you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Professional OT support and development is provided from the on-site OT Clinical Leads (Band 8a) in conjunction with the OT/PT Clinical Lead. We provide a Trust-wide Band 6 Evidence-Based Practice Programme and regular site-based in-service training. We have strong links with our Quality Improvement (QI) Team and will provide support and training on QI processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The rotations at Whipps Cross University Hospital provide a fantastic opportunity to develop and consolidate skills in the following settings:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hand Therapy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stroke and Neurotherapy Pathway&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Orthopaedics&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Surgery, Critical Care and Amputees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medicine and Palliative Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Older People Services / Care of the Elderly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Emergency Therapy Team (Emergency Department and Acute Assessment Units)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The service operates a seven day service covering core hours between 8am and 6pm. You will need to be a versatile, adaptable team player who is prepared to work across a 7 day rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The occupational therapy service has a supportive education program and robust personal development program to support staff in their learning and development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;There is a strong commitment to staff development and service improvement with support for training at Master’s level.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information please contact Brad Hodgekiss on 02085395522 then page 2698 or via email bradley.hodgekiss@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Brad Hodgekiss - Clinical Lead OT on 02085395522 then page 174 or via email brad.hodgekiss@bartshealth.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
